  "version_update": {
    "version": "0.277.0",
    "release_date": "2026-05-07",
    "changes": [
      "Pirates now patrol into low-security empire systems (police level 20 or below). Higher-security empire cores remain pirate-free. Frontier empire space is no longer perfectly safe.",
      "When police engage a pirate scout, they announce it in system chat. When they engage a raider group, they announce that reinforcements are coming.",
      "Each empire's capital fleet now responds to raider incursions in their territory — the lead ship broadcasts a departure message naming the target system, and the fleet arrives to join or initiate combat against any remaining pirates before returning home.",
      "Police engage pirates immediately on detection; the player-facing warning and dwell period only applies to player targets."
    ]
  },
